<br>Who smells gold and slays his brother."</i>
<p>--Pagan Saying</center>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tekka>Tekka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/02 10:00:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1034.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need Cash!</span><hr size=1> First rule of being cheap, stop buying rations, get a fishing pole, or buy chunks of meat you find on vendors.  Half the price and last just as long.  Second, have strong teeth, buy milk.  Do not buy muffins as they don't last as long.<br>
<br>
Second, you are level 6 and probably not KOS to the guys in east commons, kill stuff there.  The orcs carry change and weapons as well.  I leveled to 15 in EC and WC and didnt have a twink.  Get a magic weapon of any kind.  If you message me ingame I might be able to swing one your way for free.  Kill wisps when you can, at level 9 you should be able to waste them left and right.  You have to have a magic weapon though.  There is a quest you can take your greater lightstones to and make lots of money.<br>
<br>
Third, if you are not KOS in the Erud place, it might be a great place for you to go.  Warrens can not be beat.<br>
<br>
Later<br>
Tekka <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/6/02 11:43:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1034.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks!</span><hr size=1> Hmm...thanks alot for the advice, I think I might head to the Commons.  I don't know much about killing wisps - my human shadowknight a few characters ago grew stale at about 7th level.<br>
<br>
As for the Warrens, yeah, they're great.  I've thought of heading there through the Nexus, but someone told me Dark Elves are KOS to Heretics and I don't know if I'm up for traveling to Shadowhaven every time I unload.  I still might go there for some unique weapons and selling kobold molars.<br>
<br>
